==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water telescope
<hw>Water telescope</hw>. <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Optics)</fld> <def>A
telescope in which the medium between the objective and the eye piece is
water instead of air, used in some experiments in aberration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A telescope devised for looking into a body of
water.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water tender</ent>⟦br⟧
